"I cried out, 'I am slipping!' but your unfailing love, O Lord, supported me. When doubts filled my mind, your comfort gave me renewed hope and cheer." - Psalm 94:18 (NLT)

In Christ, we have His blessing within us. Yet, we may sometimes feel we are "slipping" away from God's peace during hard times that overwhelm us. But even our cries can be prayers of power, knowing that the Lord will support us, no matter how heavy our burden may be.

Even when doubts fill our mind, the comfort of the Lord‚Äôs promises can cast off those doubts as we allow His hope to renew us. We can experiencing these promises more and more as we practice His presence and His Word daily. He is the God of renewal and restoration in all ways! Thank you, Lord!

Be blessed,
Brother Johnny

